# What I Did

Step 1 — Locate all target files across the file system
- Used the find command with multiple -name flags combined using -o (OR) to locate all 12 target files in a single pass, suppressing permission errors with 2>/dev/null:
```
find / -type f \( -name 8V2L -o -name bny0 -o -name c4ZX -o -name D8B3 -o -name FHl1 -o -name oiM0 -o -name PFbD -o -name rmfX -o -name SRSq -o -name uqyw -o -name v2Vb -o -name X1Uy \) 2>/dev/null
```
- Located all file paths:
  - /mnt/D8B3
  - /mnt/c4ZX
  - /var/FHl1
  - /var/log/uqyw
  - /opt/PFbD
  - /media/rmfX
  - /etc/8V2L
  - /etc/ssh/SRSq
  - /home/v2Vb
  - /X1Uy

Step 2 — Find files owned by best-group
- Ran a group-based find from the home directory:
```
find -group best-group
```
- Returned: ./mnt/D8B3 and ./home/v2Vb

Step 3 — Find the file containing an IP address
- Used grep with a regex pattern for IPv4 addresses across all target files:
```
find / -exec grep -l '[0-9][0-9][.][0-9][0-9][.][0-9][0-9][.][0-9][0-9]' {} \; 2>/dev/null
```
- Identified the file containing an IP address: oiM0

Step 4 — Find the file matching a specific SHA1 hash
- Ran sha1sum against all target files simultaneously:
```
find / \( -name 8V2L -o -name bny0 -o -name c4ZX -o -name D8B3 -o -name FHl1 -o -name oiM0 -o -name PFbD -o -name rmfX -o -name SRSq -o -name uqyw -o -name v2Vb -o -name X1Uy \) -exec sha1sum {} \; 2>/dev/null
```
- Matched hash 9d54da7584015647ba052173b84d45e8007eba94 to file: c4ZX

Step 5 — Find the file containing 230 lines
- Used wc -l across all target files:
```
find / \( -name 8V2L -o -name bny0 -o -name c4ZX -o -name D8B3 -o -name FHl1 -o -name oiM0 -o -name PFbD -o -name rmfX -o -name SRSq -o -name uqyw -o -name v2Vb -o -name X1Uy \) -type f -exec wc -l {} \;
```
- Identified the file with 230 lines: bny0

Step 6 — Find the file whose owner has UID 502
- Used ls -ln to display numeric user and group IDs for all target files:
```
find / \( -name 8V2L -o -name bny0 -o -name c4ZX -o -name D8B3 -o -name FHl1 -o -name oiM0 -o -name PFbD -o -name rmfX -o -name SRSq -o -name uqyw -o -name v2Vb -o -name X1Uy \) -exec ls -ln {} \; 2>/dev/null
```
- Found: -rw-rw-r-- 1 502 501 ... /X1Uy confirming owner UID 502: X1Uy

Step 7 — Find the file executable by everyone
- Used the same ls -ln output from Step 6 to check file permissions.
- Found: -rwxrwxr-x 1 501 501 ... /etc/8V2L confirming world-executable permissions: 8V2L

